TABLE 1: MS COCO [11] Results We compare to state-of-the-art methods for mask mAP and speed on COCO test-dev and 
include several ablations of our base model, varying backbone network and image size. We denote the backbone architecture with 
network-depth-features, where R and D refer to ResNet [10] and DarkNet [1], respectively. Our base model, YOLACT-
550 with ResNet-101, is 3.9x faster than the previous fastest approach with competitive mask mAP. Our YOLACT++-550 model 
with ResNet-50 has the same speed while improving the performance of the base model by 4.3 mAP. Compared to Mask R-CNN, 
YOLACT++-R-50 is 3.9x faster and falls behind by only 1.6 mAP.
